==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Major general
<hw>Ma"jor gen"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An officer of the army
holding a rank next above that of brigadier general and next below that
of lieutenant general, and who usually commands a division or a
corps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Majority</ent>⟦br⟧
